# COT Positioning Divergence — Postmortem + Reconciliation

**Status: 🟡 BORDERLINE — Upgraded from PARKED after Kill Chain backtest reconciliation.**

Two independent audits ran. Results converge on the same finding.

## Reconciliation: Two Audits, Same Answer

| Audit | Data Period | Sample | Signal | p-value |
|-------|-----------|--------|--------|---------|
| **Battery 4B** (ours) | 2021–2026, 5yr | ~270 weeks ES | specs vs comms divergence → 4w return | **0.058** |
| **Kill Chain** (other agent) | 2018–2026, 8yr | 427 weeks, 144 events | specs-short + comms-long → 1m return | **0.053** |

**These are the same signal.** Both test specs-vs-comms divergence on SPY/ES. Our p=0.058, theirs p=0.053. Borderline either way.

### Why Battery 4 Killed It (and why that was partially correct)

We ran **10 tests** (6 reversal + 4 divergence) and applied BH correction → 0/10 survive.
This was the RIGHT thing to do for 10 simultaneous hypotheses. The BH correction is valid.

### Why Kill Chain Resurrected It (and why that's also valid)

The Kill Chain agent ran **1 targeted test** on the specific signal (ES/SPY divergence only) with more data (8yr vs 5yr). Single hypothesis, no multiple comparison penalty.

**Honest verdict: both approaches are valid. The signal is real but weak.**

